The power utility said some of its emergency generators were supplementing the available generation capacity. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has announced that its power system remains constrained but there will be no load shedding on Monday. The power utility said some of its emergency generators were supplementing the available generation capacity. The embattled utility said the emergency generators would be replenished to ensure that they were at adequate levels to meet the demand for the week ahead. Eskom has asked that customers use electricity sparingly as they monitor the power systems. #POWERALERT 2Date: 19 January 2020The power system continues to be resilient with no loadshedding expected tomorrow @SABCNewsOnline @IOL @ewnupdates @eNCA @TimesLIVE @dailymaverick @SowetanLIVE @TheCitizen_News @News24 pic.twitter.com/lCR4Ccnimy 